%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20shrinking%20birth%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20isn't%20one%20economic%20or%20cultural%20reason%20as%20to%20why%20so%20many%20millennials%20are%20two-and-done%20with%20having%20kids.%20While%20childcare%20costs%20and%20fertility%20issues%20play%20substantial%20roles%2C%20there%20has%20also%20been%20a%20sea%20change%20in%20what%20an%20ideal%20family%20%E2%80%94%20and%20family%20size%20%E2%80%94%20looks%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a3548db-cd99-4edb-8d6a-f741280d0db8%5C%22%3EBarely%20making%20do%20with%20two%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20family%20size%2C%20millennials%20aren't%20that%20different%20from%20their%20predecessors.%20According%20to%20a%202020%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20Report%2C%20millennial%20women%20average%202.02%20kids.%20At%20similar%20ages%2C%20Gen%20X%20women%20had%202.05%20kids%20and%20boomers%202.07.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fzefjq%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fzefjq%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flsa.umich.edu%2Fsoc%2Fpeople%2Ffaculty%2Fpjsmock.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPamela%20Smock%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20sociology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20said%20having%20two%20kids%20has%20been%20an%20American%20ideal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F718084%2Faverage-number-of-own-children-per-family%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esince%20the%201960s%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20difference%20between%20the%20generations%20is%20that%20millennials%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20kids%20than%20previous%20generations.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%20a%20young%20family%20with%20two%20kids%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20norm%2C%20but%2C%20for%20some%2C%20a%20symbol%20of%20luxury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20see%20marriage%20and%20childbearing%20as%20something%20to%20do%20once%20they%20feel%20economically%20comfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20Smock%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20many%2C%20that%20means%20not%20having%20any%20debt%20and%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20mortgage.%20The%20average%20millennial%20borrower%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Floans%2Fstudent-loans%2Fstudent-loan-debt-by-generation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eowes%20%2442%2C000%20in%20student%20loan%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20part%20of%20why%20it's%20so%20difficult%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-cant-millennials-buy-homes-first-time-buyers-mortgage-rates-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennials%20to%20buy%20their%20first%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Comparatively%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconreview.studentorg.berkeley.edu%2Fbaby-boomers-and-the-future-of-homeownership-in-the-united-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E45%25%20of%20baby%20boomers%3C%2Fa%3E%20bought%20their%20first%20homes%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2025%20and%2034.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221936%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20family%20in%20the%201950s%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687e4f5585e81483682e5b6f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221452%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHaving%20two%20kids%20was%20always%20closer%20to%20the%20American%20norm.%20It's%20just%20more%20of%20a%20luxury%20now.%3Cp%3EStockbyte%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWork%20has%20also%20changed%2C%20Smock%20said.%20Gone%20are%20the%20lifelong%20jobs%20that%20require%20a%20basic%20college%20degree.%20Millennials%20are%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F231587%2Fmillennials-job-hopping-generation.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob-hopping%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20also%20impacts%20their%20sense%20of%20security%20as%20costs%20keep%20rising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephanie%20Fornaro%2C%20a%2040-year-old%20mom%20of%20two%20in%20Dallas%2C%20has%20a%2020-year-old%20daughter%20in%20college%20and%20a%207-year-old%20son.%20She%20had%20her%20daughter%20when%20she%20was%2020%2C%20but%20delayed%20having%20her%20son%20until%20her%20early%2030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinancially%2C%20I%20was%20in%20a%20different%20season%20in%20my%20life%20to%20afford%20a%20second%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20she%20divorced%20a%20few%20years%20after%20giving%20birth%20to%20her%20daughter.%20It%20was%20only%20when%20she%20remarried%20in%202017%20that%20she%20felt%20secure%20enough%20to%20have%20another%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.binghamton.edu%2Fsociology%2Ffaculty%2Fprofile.html%3Fid%3Dwchoudary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWendie%20N.%20Choudary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20sociologist%20and%20lecturer%20at%20Binghamton%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20in%20addition%20to%20rent%20or%20housing%20costs%2C%20millennial%20parents%20also%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-paid-over-fifty-thousand-dollars-for-childcare-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eastronomically%20high%20childcare%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20paying%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F05%2F15%2Fbusiness%2Fchild-care-cost-average-annual%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannual%20average%20of%20%2411%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFornaro%2C%20who%20founded%20and%20runs%20a%20national%20childcare%20agency%2C%20said%20a%20third%20child%20would%20have%20a%20huge%20financial%20impact%20on%20her%20family.%20To%20keep%20up%20with%20her%20job%2C%20she%20would%20need%20a%20full-time%2