2030s%20or%20early%2040s%20might%20not%20feel%20the%20risk%20is%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20a%20rough%20pregnancy%20is%20enough%20to%20deter%20wanting%20more%20kids.%20Lamson%2C%20who%20had%20her%20first%20child%20at%2031%20and%20second%20at%2036%2C%20felt%20a%20huge%20difference%20in%20those%20five%20years.%20At%2031%2C%20she%20said%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20stay%20very%20active%20and%20exercise%20four%20times%20a%20week.%20The%20second%20time%20was%20more%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20really%20low%20energy%20throughout%20my%20entire%20pregnancy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20struggled%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20pain%2C%20so%20even%20when%20I%20would%20try%20to%20just%20get%20out%20and%20walk%2C%20I%20could%20only%20kind%20of%20do%20so%20for%20a%20period%20of%20time%20before%20I%20didn't%20feel%20all%20that%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20attribute%20it%20a%20lot%20to%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20she%20ended%20up%20going%20to%20physical%20therapy%20to%20alleviate%20some%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22145649e4-a458-47a5-b475-2d8abbcda548%5C%22%3EWith%20more%20choice%2C%20parents%20choose%20fewer%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20vintage%20photo%20of%20a%20family%20in%20the%201900s%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687e5024f748d8c055f5f53b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWith%20more%20freedom%2C%20parents%20are%20choosing%20to%20have%20fewer%20kids.%3Cp%3Ekerkla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20World%20War%20II%2C%20it%20was%20normal%20to%20get%20married%20at%2019%20and%20have%20kids%20in%20rapid%20succession%2C%20Smock%20said.%20But%20with%20more%20choices%2C%20millennials%20realized%20%26quot%3Bthey%20don't%20have%20to%20follow%20the%20path%20that%20their%20parents%20and%20grandparents%20took%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20there's%20been%20an%20increased%20online%20interest%20in%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrad-wife-on-tiktok-shares-idyllic-lifestyle-risks-money-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrad%20wives%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eviemagazine.com%2Fpost%2Fnew-poll-found-half-of-americans-now-want-big-family%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emerits%20of%20large%20families%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20it%20hasn't%20shown%20much%20of%20a%20dent%20in%20what%20most%20people%20want%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsociology.northwestern.edu%2Fpeople%2Ffaculty%2Fcore%2Fjulia-behrman.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJulia%20A.%20Behrman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20sociology%20at%20Northwestern%20University%20who%20researches%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fread.dukeupress.edu%2Fdemography%2Farticle-abstract%2F61%2F5%2F1535%2F391169%2FIdeal-Family-Size-and-Reproductive-Orientations-An%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evalues%20shape%20a%20person's%20ideal%20family%20size%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20pretty%20consistently%20seeing%20these%20average%20ideal%20family%20sizes%20of%20about%202.5%2C%26quot%3B%20Behrman%20said.%20Most%20actually%20plan%20to%20have%20fewer%3A%20roughly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2025%2F06%2F18%2Fus-adults-in-their-20s-and-30s-plan-to-have-fewer-children-than-in-the-past%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1.8%20on%20average%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20people%20in%20their%2020s%20and%2030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Behrman's%20research%2C%20she's%20found%20that%20people%20with%20more%20progressive%20views%20on%20gender%20norms%20and%20household%20labor%20tend%20to%20want%20fewer%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20often%20because%20they%20are%20aware%20of%20how%20childrearing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstay-at-home-dad-breadwinner-mom-double-standards-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisproportionately%20falls%20on%20mothers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20parents%20want%20two%20or%20more%20kids%2C%20Behrman's%20research%20found%20that%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20their%20top%20priority.%20Other%20aspects%20of%20family%20life%2C%20like%20financial%20stability%2C%20rank%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20parents%20who%20can%20technically%20swing%20three%20kids%2C%20it%20could%20mean%20a%20notable%20decline%20in%20their%20quality%20of%20life.%20Fornaro%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20as%20one%20of%20eight%20children%20and%20felt%20neglected%20because%20her%20dad%20and%20stepmom%20struggled%20to%20raise%20them%20all%2C%20doesn't%20want%20her%20kids%20to%20experience%20the%20same.%20She%20said%20having%20a%20third%20wouldn't%20just%20impact%20how%20much%20she%20could%20contribute%20to%20her%20kids'%20college%20tuition%20or%20inheritances.%20It%20would%20also%20change%20how%20much%20time%20she%20gets%20to%20spend%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20a%20pretty%20active%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Traveling%20and%20going%20on%20their%20boat%20would%20be%20harder%20with%20an%20infant.%20Taking%20her%20son%20to%20his%20extracurriculars%20%E2%80%94%20jujitsu%2C%20baseball%2C%20and%20football%20%E2%80%94%20would%20also%20be%20much%20harder%20with%20a%20newborn.%20And%20with%20Fornaro's%20daughter%20in%20college%2C%20caring%20for%20a%20baby%20would%20make%20it%20difficult%20for%20Fornaro%20to%20visit%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221625%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20parents%20with%20their%20two%20kids%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687e509985e81483682e5b88%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221219%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20parents%20feel%20that%20caring%20for%20more%20than%20two%20kids%20would%20reduce%20