20with%20OpenAI%20fell%20apart.%3Cp%3EIllustration%20by%20Thomas%20Fuller%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20kind%20of%20dealmaking%20sweeping%20Silicon%20Valley%20is%20dividing%20employees%20into%20haves%20and%20have-nots.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestors%20and%20founders%20say%20it%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20for%20job%20candidates%20to%20do%20careful%20diligence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20most%20crucial%20thing%20to%20assess%20is%20how%20much%20you%20trust%20the%20founder%2C%20multiple%20investors%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20dealmaking%20is%20sweeping%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20forcing%20employees%20to%20be%20vigilant%20about%20how%20much%20trust%20they%20are%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20startup%20founders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20instead%20of%20acquiring%20AI%20startups%20outright%2C%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20have%20been%20licensing%20their%20technology%20or%20making%20deals%20for%20top%20talent%2C%20with%20startup%20employees%20sometimes%20getting%20divided%20into%20separate%20camps%20of%20haves%20and%20have-nots.%20Those%20with%20the%20most%20desirable%20AI%20skills%20reap%20a%20windfall%20while%20those%20who%20remain%20are%20shrouded%20in%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20recently%20happened%20to%20Windsurf%20employees%20after%20the%20AI%20coding%20company%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20being%20acquired%20by%20OpenAI%20for%20%243%20billion%2C%20but%20was%20instead%20split%20in%20half.%20Google%20paid%20billions%20to%20hire%20Windsurf's%20CEO%20and%20top%20talent%2C%20and%20the%20hundreds%20of%20employees%20who%20remained%20were%20bought%20by%20another%20startup%2C%20Cognition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%20for%20startup%20employees%2C%20many%20investors%20expect%20these%20kinds%20of%20novel%20transactions%20to%20continue%20as%20the%20velocity%20of%20developments%20in%20AI%20makes%20companies%20unlikely%20to%20want%20to%20wait%20months%20or%20years%20for%20regulatory%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d9f7b75-5ab5-4429-a4b5-9711f40803fc%5C%22%3ECandidates%20need%20to%20ask%20tough%20questions%20about%20the%20founder%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20traditional%20M%26amp%3BA%20has%20mostly%20gone%20out%20the%20window%2C%20it%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20for%20startup%20employees%20to%20do%20their%20homework%2C%20advises%20Steve%20Brotman%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20Alpha%20Partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20light%20of%20what%20we%20just%20saw%20with%20Windsurf%2C%20it's%20crucial%20to%20understand%20the%20ownership%20dynamics%2C%26quot%3B%20Brotman%20said.%20%26quot%3B%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20working%20100-hour%20weeks%20only%20to%20realize%20your%20options%20are%20underwater%20or%20your%20exit%20upside%20is%20capped.%20And%20remember%3A%20companies%20that%20are%20transparent%20and%20deliberate%20about%20governance%20tend%20to%20be%20better%20long-term%20bets%2C%20both%20for%20your%20career%20and%20your%20equity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAsk%20hard%20questions%20about%20runway%2C%20revenue%2C%20burn%2C%20and%20investor%20syndicate%20quality%2C%26quot%3B%20Brotman%20continued.%20%26quot%3BWho's%20on%20the%20board%3F%20Are%20they%20structured%20for%20long-term%20growth%20or%20a%20quick%20flip%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20candidates%20should%20assess%20is%20how%20much%20they%20trust%20the%20founder%2C%20according%20to%20Deedy%20Das%2C%20an%20investor%20at%20Menlo%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20wants%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20founders%20control%20almost%20everything%20that%20happens%20in%20a%20company%2C%20including%20how%20you%20get%20paid%2C%20when%20you%20get%20paid%2C%20how%20the%20equity%20vests%2C%20and%20when%20you%20can%20sell%20the%20equity%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Das.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20everything%2C%20so%20having%20trust%20in%20your%20founder%20to%20do%20the%20right%20thing%20by%20the%20team%20is%20extremely%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20investors%20would%20typically%20research%20a%20founder%20before%20writing%20a%20check%20to%20one%20of%20their%20many%20portfolio%20companies%2C%20prospective%20employees%20should%20ask%20around%20about%20founders%20whom%20they%20could%20be%20tied%20to%20for%20years%2C%20said%20Hari%20Raghavan%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Autograph.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20should%20be%20doing%20diligence%20on%20whether%20this%20is%20a%20standup%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Raghavan.%20%26quot%3BDo%20your%20best%20to%20suss%20out%2C%20'Are%20these%20guys%20going%20to%20take%20care%20of%20me%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaghavan%20suggests%20that%20founders%20should%20sign%20a%20written%20pledge%20agreeing%20to%20treat%20employees%20well%20in%20terms%20of%20stock%20options%20and%20exit%20scenarios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20things%20that%20any%20good%20founder%20should%20be%20doing%2C%20and%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20good%20ones%20do%2C%20but%20I%20think%20even%20just%20establishing%20that%20set%20of%20rules%20is%20a%20good%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProspective%20employees%20should%20not%20be%20afraid%20to%20%26quot%3Binterrogate%26quot%3B%20a%20founder%20on%20how%20they%20are%20thinking%20about%20an%20exit%2C%20according%20to%20Jake%20Saper%2C%20a%20general%20partner%20at%20Emergence%20Capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAsk%20founders%20how%20they%20would%20weigh%20staying%20independent%2C%20a%20classic%20acquisition%2C%20or%20a%20licensing%20deal%20that%20carves%20out%20key%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Saper%20said.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20answer%20tells%20you%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20journey%20you're%20signing%20up%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScrutinizing%20the%20fine%20print%20has%20also%20become%20more%20important%2C%20said%20Saper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMake%20sure%20offer%20letters%20and%20stock%20agreements%20spell%20out%20vesting%20acceleration%2C%20treatment%20of%20options%2C%20and%20retention%20bonuses%20if%20only%20'substantially%20all'%20of%20the%20team%20moves%2C%26quot%3B%20Saper%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20clauses%20mattered%20at%20Inflection%20and%20Windsurf%2C%20and%20they%20will%20matter%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20Microsoft%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-hired-inflection-team-amid-board-concerns-about-openai-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehired%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20founder%20of%20Inflection%20AI%2C%20Mustafa%20Suleyman%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20startup's%20staff%20to%20help%20lead%20its%20AI%20efforts.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20June%2C%20Meta%20paid%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scale-ai-15-billion-alexandr-wang-acquihire-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%2414%20billion%20for%20a%2049%20percent%20stake%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20data%20labeling%20company%20Scale%20AI%20and%20hired%20its%20founder%2C%20Alexandr%20Wang%2C%20to%20run%20its%20Superintelligence%20group.%20Meta%20also%20hired%20some%20of%20the%20startup's%20researchers.%20Last%20week%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscale-ai-layoffs-citing-overhiring-unprofitability-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EScale%20AI%20laid%20off%2014%25%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20its%20workforce%2C%20or%20200%20employees%2C%20and%20revealed%20it%20is%20unprofitable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20Saper%20says%20to%20take%20a%20hard%20look%20at%20the%20underlying%20business%20model%20of%20a%20startup%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20can%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStartups%20with%20unique%20data%20feeds%2C%20embedded%20distribution%20or%20clear%20recurring%20revenue%20have%20leverage%20to%20stay%20independent%2C%26quot%3B%20Saper%20said.%