quot%3Bdifficult%20mountainous%20terrain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plane%2C%20operated%20by%20Siberian-headquartered%20Angara%20Airlines%2C%20was%20manufactured%20in%201976%2C%20making%20it%2049%20years%20old%2C%20according%20to%20state%20media%20outlet%20TASS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETASS%20reported%20that%20in%202021%2C%20this%20particular%20An-24's%20airworthiness%20certificate%20was%20extended%20to%202036%2C%20which%20would%20have%20allowed%20it%20to%20fly%20passenger%20journeys%20up%20to%2060%20years%20after%20its%20maiden%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20open-source%20Russian%20plane%20registry%20listed%20the%20crashed%20An-24%20as%20entering%20operations%20in%20February%20of%201976%2C%20making%20it%2049%20years%20and%20five%20months%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20compare%2C%20major%20international%20and%20US%20airlines%20typically%20phase%20out%20aircraft%20that%20have%20been%20in%20service%20for%20over%2035%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20Angara%20was%20also%20one%20of%20two%20Russian%20airlines%20that%20highlighted%20a%20need%20to%20extend%20the%20service%20life%20of%20its%20An-24s%2C%20saying%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsanction-hit-russia-airlines-getting-plane-parts-delivered-luggage-report-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWestern%20sanctions%20had%20limited%20access%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20maintenance%20workers%20and%20spare%20parts%20for%20much%20of%20its%20fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20today%20working%20in%20a%20market%20in%20which%20there%20are%20no%20alternatives%20to%20the%20An-24%20and%20An-26%2C%26quot%3B%20Angara%20deputy%20CEO%20Sergei%20Zorin%20said%20at%20the%20time%2C%20per%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAviation%20authorities%20signed%20a%20contract%20in%20March%20to%20push%20the%20aircraft's%20service%20life%20to%2060%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20media%20also%20reported%20on%20Thursday%20that%20the%20crashed%20An-24%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-planes-safety-incidents-maintenance-sanctions-spare-parts-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esustained%20damage%20and%20equipment%20failures%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20three%20times%20in%20the%20past%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiting%20Russia's%20federal%20air%20transport%20agency%2C%20TASS%20reported%20that%20the%20plane%20had%20rolled%20off%20a%20runway%20in%202018%20and%20clipped%20a%20lightning%20pole%20with%20its%20left%20wing.%20The%20aircraft%20also%20returned%20to%20an%20airport%20in%202019%20after%20its%20generator%20failed%2C%20while%20one%20of%20its%20radio%20sets%20was%20reported%20to%20have%20malfunctioned%20on%20the%20tarmac%20in%20May%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20approach%20warning%20system%20was%20also%20activated%20once%20in%202022%2C%20per%20TASS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20state%20media%20outlet%20reported%20preliminary%20findings%20from%20emergency%20services%20that%20crew%20error%20caused%20the%20crash%2C%20though%20it%20did%20not%20specify%20how%20authorities%20arrived%20at%20that%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESvetlana%20Petrenko%2C%20a%20spokeswoman%20for%20Russia's%20Investigative%20Committee%2C%20said%20on%20Thursday%20that%20her%20office%20would%20launch%20a%20criminal%20investigation%20into%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAngara%20Airlines%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-extend-antonov-plane-life-50-years-crash-dozens-aboard-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753421230000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6882fa2985e81483682ea71a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-extend-antonov-plane-life-50-years-crash-dozens-aboard-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20crashed%20An-24%2C%20a%20twin-pr