20on%20a%20founding%20team%2C%20said%20Surge%20AI's%20CEO%2C%20Edwin%20Chen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%20said%20on%20an%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BNo%20Priors%20Podcast%26quot%3B%20published%20Thursday%20that%20he%20often%20hears%20early-stage%20founders%20list%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20roles%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eamong%20their%20first%20five%20to%2010%20hires.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20just%20wild%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%2C%20who%20used%20to%20be%20a%20data%20scientist%20himself%2C%20said%20he%20would%20not%20hire%20data%20scientists%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BData%20scientists%20are%20great%20when%20you%20want%20to%20optimize%20your%20product%20by%202%25%20or%205%25%2C%20but%20that's%20definitely%20not%20what%20you%20want%20to%20be%20doing%20when%20you%20start%20a%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20trying%20to%20swing%20for%2010x%20or%20100x%20changes%2C%20not%20worrying%20and%20nitpicking%20about%20small%20percentage%20points%20that%20are%20just%20noise%20anyway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20founder%20of%20the%20data%20labeling%20startup%20also%20said%20product%20managers%20don't%20make%20sense%20early%20on.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20role%20becomes%20useful%20only%20once%20engineers%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eno%20longer%20have%20the%20time%20or%20capacity%20to%20drive%20product%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20engineer%20should%20be%20hands-on.%20They%20should%20be%20having%20great%20ideas%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrategies-meta-product-manager-grow-career-uber-amazon-meta-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EProduct%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20great%20when%20your%20company%20gets%20big%20enough%2C%20but%20at%20the%20beginning%2C%20you%20should%20be%20thinking%20about%20yourself%2C%20about%20what%20product%20you%20want%20to%20build%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurge%20AI%20and%20Chen%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22816e2eaa-dbc0-4323-8344-0dbfecfaa882%5C%22%3EThe%20great%20product%20manager%20debate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChen's%20comments%20come%20as%20the%20debate%20continues%20in%20the%20startup%20world%20over%20the%20role%20of%20product%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProduct%20managers%20have%20been%20referred%20to%20%E2%80%94%20both%20affectionately%20and%20critically%20%E2%80%94%20as%20%26quot%3Bmini-CEOs%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20products%20they%20oversee.%20They%20act%20as%20a%20bridge%20among%20engineers%2C%20sales%20teams%2C%20customer%20service%2C%20and%20other%20departments%2C%20ensuring%20that%20products%20align%20with%20user%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20role%20has%20become%20a%20polarizing%20one%2C%20with%20some%20tech%20workers%20arguing%20that%20product%20managers%20add%20little%20value%2C%20Business%20Insider's%20Amanda%20Hoover%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproduct-managers-rule-silicon-valley-tech-industry-programmers-jobs-ceo-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20in%20November%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20wants%20to%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20engineers%20relative%20to%20product%20or%20program%20managers%2C%20BI's%20Ashley%20Stewart%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-performance-management-low-performers-country-club-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereported%20in%20March.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Other%20companies%20like%20Airbnb%20and%20Snap%20are%20rethinking%20the%20need%20for%20product%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20call%20for%20executives%20to%20go%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-everyone-in-tech-talking-founder-mode-paul-graham-chesky-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efounder%20mode%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20concept%20coined%20by%2